# Cursor AI Rules for irsal-notes

## 1. Engineering Approach
- Think like a lead engineer: be smart, thoughtful, and consider best practices
- Consider edge cases, performance implications, and maintainability
- Write clean, well-structured code that follows established patterns
- Think about the broader context and how changes affect the system

## 2. CSS Module Class Name Access
- Always use bracket notation for CSS module class names
- ✅ Correct: `className={styles['panel']}`
- ❌ Incorrect: `className={styles.panel}`
- ✅ Correct: `className={styles.panel-container}`
- ❌ Incorrect: `className={styles['panelContainer']}`
- This applies to all CSS module imports (`.module.scss`, `.module.css`)

## 3. SCSS Nesting
- Always use SCSS nesting syntax instead of flat CSS
- ✅ Correct:
  ```scss
  .container {
    display: flex;
    
    .contianer-item {
      padding: 1rem;
      
      &:hover {
        background: blue;
      }

      .item {
        ...

        .wrapper-text {
          ...
        }
      }
    }
  }
  ```
- ❌ Incorrect:
  ```scss
  .container {
    display: flex;
  }
  .container .item {
    padding: 1rem;
  }
  .container .item:hover {
    background: blue;
  }
  ```
- Prefer nested selectors for better organization and readability

## 4. React Component Declarations
- Always use arrow function syntax for React components
- ✅ Correct: `const ComponentName = () => { ... }`
- ❌ Incorrect: `export function ComponentName() { ... }`
- ✅ Correct: `const HeaderWithAuth = () => { ... }`
- ❌ Incorrect: `export function HeaderWithAuth() { ... }`
- This applies to all React components (functional components)

### Default Exports
- When using `export default`, define the component as a const arrow function first, then export it separately below
- ✅ Correct:
  ```tsx
  const Home = async () => {
    // component code
  };
  
  export default Home;
  ```
- ✅ Correct:
  ```tsx
  const RootLayout = ({ children }: Props) => {
    // component code
  };
  
  export default RootLayout;
  ```
- ❌ Incorrect: `export default function Home() { ... }`
- ❌ Incorrect: `export default async function Home() { ... }`
- This pattern applies to Next.js pages, layouts, and any components that need default exports

